books.author: Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay
books.description: Pather Dabi is a notable Bengali novel written by Saratchandra Chattopadhyay, first published in 1926. The title translates to THE DEMAND OF THE PATH and the novel is recognized for its revolutionary themes and its impact on the Indian independence movement.
books.title: Pother Dabi

books.author: Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay
books.title: Dutta
books.description: Dutta is a renowned novel by Saratchandra Chattopadhyay, a distinguished figure in Bengali literature. Published in 1917, Dutta is a compelling narrative that delves into themes of love, duty, and societal expectations. The novel is admired for its rich character development, emotional depth, and critique of social norms.

books.author: Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay
books.title: Srikanta
books.description: Srikanta,is one of the most celebrated works of Saratchandra Chattopadhyay, a prolific Bengali novelist and short story writer. First published in four parts between 1917 and 1933, the novel is known for its exploration of the complexities of human relationships, social issues, and philosophical introspection.

books.author: Satyajit Ray
books.title: Phare feluda
books.description: Pahare feluda is a detective novel written by the renowned Indian filmmaker and writer Satyajit Ray. It is part of the famous Feluda series, which follows the adventures of the private detective Pradosh Chandra Mitter, commonly known as Feluda, along with his cousin Tapesh Ranjan Mitter (Topshe) and the humorous and knowledgeable writer Lalmohan Ganguly (Jatayu).

books.author: Manik Bandopadhyay
books.title: neki
books.description: neki(also spelled as neeki)is a notable work by Manik Bandopadhyay, a prominent Bengali writer known for his realistic and humanistic portrayals of rural and urban life in Bengal. Manik Bandopadhyay's works often delve into the complexities of human nature and societal structures, and neki is no exception.

books.author: Sunil Gangopadhyay
books.title: Andar Mahal
books.description: Andar mahal by Sunil Gangopadhyay is a distinguished work in Bengali literature. Sunil Gangopadhyay, a prolific writer and poet, explores the complex and often concealed lives within traditional Bengali households in this novel.

books.author: Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay
books.title: Mahesh
books.description: Saratchandra Mahesh, better known as Saratchandra Chattopadhyay, is one of the most celebrated and influential Bengali novelists of the early 20th century. Born on September 15, 1876, in Debanandapur, Bengal Presidency, British India (now in West Bengal, India), Saratchandra's works have left an indelible mark on Bengali literature and Indian literature as a whole.

books.author: Manik Bandopadhyay
books.title: Podda Nodir Majhi
books.description: Podda Nodir Majhi(The Boatman of the Padma River) is one of the most acclaimed novels by Manik Bandopadhyay, a revered figure in Bengali literature. First published in 1936, the novel is renowned for its realistic depiction of life along the Padma River and its exploration of human suffering, resilience, and the socio-economic struggles of rural Bengal.
